      "content": "interesting. i was reading something online a bit ago though that suggested things might have changed regardless because of the economy or just general social shifts at the time, and that maybe some of the more radical groups were actually the ones that made the government nervous enough to settle. do historians think the nonviolent approach was the only way it could've worked, or is that just the main way it's taught?",
